        "name": "",
        "username": "desert_nip",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-11T12:52:59.223Z",
        "cooked": "<p>It is also important to add that Signal can <em>not</em> protect against a truly compromised OS/device. The only reason the anti-recall feature works, is because Windows choses to expose a DRM flag which developers can set to prevent screen capture of their app. And the same goes for any other OS. If your device is truly compromised (or Windows were to remove the flag for example), there is nothing Signal could do to prevent capture.</p>\n<p>No app can ever be safer than the device you are running it on.</p>",
